story.title: Ugly Duckling - Part 4

author.bio: Frank Anthony Polito is an award-winning author and playwright. His published books and plays can be found on Amazon.com. He lives in the Detroit suburb of Pleasant Ridge.

story.storyDescription: Bella would give anything to be pretty. But looks can be deceiving.
story.prePaywallNotification: Which is better: a beautiful face or a beautiful voice? See what Bella decides in UGLY DUCKLING.
story.postPaywallNotification: Who is watching Bella?! Find out in UGLY DUCKLING.

messages.text: I need to talk to you.
What more can I do for you, dear Bella?
I made you beautiful. Isn’t that what you wanted?
Beau just dumped me in front of the entire school.
When I got up in front of everyone and couldn’t sing…
And said I didn’t deserve to be queen ☹
Everyone was laughing and making fun of me.
What about all of your pretty new friends?
They’re not my friends. At least not anymore.
I guess they never really were…
But I thought Beau really liked me.
Perhaps you’re better off without him?
He’s the hottest guy in school.
Beauty is bought by judgment of the eye.
I don’t think I want to be pretty anymore.
I thought things would be different…
I did nothing of the sort dear.
I simply gave what you asked.
What did you think, Bella dear?
I thought once I was pretty, I would have friends.
But I’m lonelier than I’ve ever been before.
I want my voice back! I want to sing again!
I’m in SO much pain, Fairy Godmother.
When I had my voice, I could sing to take the pain away.
Bella breaks down again and starts sobbing uncontrollably.
Remember what I told you - I will take care of everything.
Please give me my voice back! PLEASE!
Is that what you really want dear?
I’d rather be ugly and be able to sing...
Than be beautiful on the outside, but sound so ugly on the inside.
Go home, and go to sleep…
When you wake in the morning, everything will be as you wish.
Bella goes home and cries herself to sleep.
I’m back to my old self!!
I literally had to pinch myself.
Bella walks through the halls at school, passing by her old friends.
Hey, troll! How’s it feel looking like a freak?!
Everyone I see makes fun of me.
It’s like Beautiful Bella never existed.
But I know what to do…
Bella goes to the music room and finds herself a quiet corner.
She closes her eyes and begins to sing.
After a moment, she feels someone watching her.
I heard you singing just now.
Maybe you’ll let me play for you sometime while you sing.
I’m thinking about starting a band. You should join me.
I don’t think I could sing in front of other people.
You mean what happened at Homecoming?
Oh god. You heard me? I sounded awful.
So you got a little stage fright.
You don’t remember me, do you?
He’s not my boyfriend anymore, by the way.
Yeah - he seemed like a real jerk.
He looks cute when he smiles.
How did you know it was me?
Right now. Don’t I look different?
I guess now that you mention it…
You do look sort of different.
No offense, but I think you look prettier without so much make-up on.
I like seeing the real you.
I like seeing your true beauty.
My name’s Cody, by the way.
You probably don’t remember, but we had a class together Freshman year.
You looked beautiful back then too.
What would you want to do?
I’d love to sing with you.
